--- Network Operations Disclaimer ---

This software creates, manages, and terminates network listeners, forwarders,
tunnels, and redirectors using socat. These operations inherently involve
binding ports, intercepting traffic, and relaying data between endpoints.
Users must ensure they have proper authorization from all relevant network
administrators and asset owners before deploying any operational mode.

The authors make no guarantees about the behavior of socat or the underlying
operating system's network stack. Network operations may interact with
firewalls, intrusion detection systems, security monitoring tools, and other
network infrastructure in unpredictable ways. Users bear sole responsibility
for understanding and managing these interactions.


--- Data Handling Notice ---

Traffic capture mode records network data to local log files. Users are
responsible for the secure handling, storage, retention, and disposal of
captured data in compliance with applicable data protection regulations
(including but not limited to GDPR, CCPA, HIPAA, PCI DSS, and similar
frameworks). The software sets restrictive file permissions (0o600) on capture
logs and private keys, but users must implement additional organizational and
technical controls appropriate to their environment.


--- Cryptographic Notice ---

This software uses OpenSSL for TLS certificate generation and encrypted tunnel
operations. The generated self-signed certificates are intended for testing and
internal use only — they do not provide identity verification. Users requiring
production-grade TLS should obtain certificates from a trusted Certificate
Authority. Export, import, or use of cryptographic software may be subject to
government regulations in certain jurisdictions.


